			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The way this EXPLOIT used to work was like this: you charm a tortured soul and then sic it on something with a different faction; once it starts to cast a spell, you click your pre-nerf CoS (which probably don't exist on your server) to break charm before the soul's spell lands.  Once the spell lands, the mob it was fighting will now be aggro on the soul.  This sets up the initial fight.  Since all the mobs there are social, you keep it going by pulling more mobs into the vicinity of that fight and then FD.
<br />

<br />
You could probably use invis potions to get around the limitation of not having a CoS, but I think you're probably stupid to try to use this exploit, for a couple of reasons:
<br />

<br />
1) GMs were watching for (and banning) people using this, since it was a well-known exploit for a long time; if it still works on your server, I would expect that fact to be common knowledge among the higher-end players and also the GMs.  And even if a GM doesn't catch you, you can still probably expect another player to report you because the nature of the exploit is such that the surrounding area is extremely hazardous for anyone else trying to exp, and that tends to piss people off.
<br />

<br />
2) this was (more or less) fixed quite a good long while ago; even if your server is on an older code base, I seriously doubt that it would be that old (developers generally prefer not to deal with split code bases and would probably sync what code they could)
<br />

<br />
In short, I doubt that it will work on your server, and even if it does, I probably still wouldn't use it anyway.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=718925" target="_blank" class="postlink">Veronis MacJuris, 65 Barbarian Prophet</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=883909" target="_blank" class="postlink">Chakek, 65 Iksar Arch Lich</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.bladesofveeshan.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Blades of Veeshan</a>, Xegony</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
