<br />

<br />
You don't need any sort of clicky invis to do this.  Hell, I just used fd to break the charm because it meant that if I miss timed things that I wouldn't have a bunch of mobs charging after me.
<br />

<br />
You pretty much much just need to send a charmed soul on a caster mob of any sort.  Once the caster begins to cast, break you charm however you want.  The mob will continue casting and hit the your ex pet, they will start to fight.  
<br />

<br />
There are 2 factions in tactics, keep pulling mobs from both factions onto the fighting mobs trying to keep them balanced.  As long as you do something, anything to get aggro you will get exp when the mobs die (gogo ceramic black band).
<br />

<br />
Using this I made a good 1 million pp at least and around 100 aas in a couple days.  With a little work and I sow you can kill the diaku overseer like this once you figure out how to get around his rampage.  You can even farm the bejesus out of glykus and make a good couple 100k every clear.  This isn't even counting the named mobs that pop, once you get good and can keep the war going for a decent period of time you'll probably get at least 3 or 4 nameds and a bagful of spectral parches and boar horns/meats.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
